   "source": [
    "# Simulation Examples\n",
    "\n",
    "First we must do some setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import chimeric_tools.Simulation as ctc\n",
    "import chimeric_tools.Data as ctd\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.lines import Line2D\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "plt.rc(\"figure\", figsize=(16, 6))\n",
    "plt.rc(\"savefig\", dpi=90)\n",
    "plt.rc(\"font\", family=\"sans-serif\")\n",
    "plt.rc(\"font\", size=14)\n",
    "\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simple Cases Simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "First we are going to do a simple simulation. We are going to simulate 1000 US cases with a block length of 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bs = ctc.COVID(geo_values = \"US\", include = [\"cases\"])\n",
    "for data in bs.simulate(block_length = 5, reps = 1000):\n",
    "    plt.plot(data[0][\"cases\"], color= \"tab:blue\", alpha = 0.1)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Weeks\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Cases\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Covid Simulation of FIP: \" + data[1])\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also plot the real cases count on-top of this plot to help visualize the simulation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bs = ctc.COVID(geo_values = \"US\", include = [\"cases\"])\n",
    "truth_data = ctd.covid_data(geo_values = \"US\", include = [\"cases\"])\n",
    "for data in bs.simulate(block_length = 5, reps = 1000):\n",
    "    plt.plot(data[0][\"cases\"], color= \"tab:blue\", alpha = 0.1)\n",
    "plt.plot(truth_data.cases, color= \"tab:red\")\n",
    "plt.plot(truth_data.preds_cases, color= \"black\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Weeks\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Cases\")\n",
    "colors = ['black', 'tab:red', 'tab:blue']\n",
    "lines = [Line2D([0], [0], color=c) for c in colors]\n",
    "labels = ['Truths', 'Prediction', 'Simulation']\n",
    "plt.legend(lines, labels)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Covid Simulation of FIP: \" + data[1])\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Bootstrapping from many FIPS\n",
    "#### Uniform Random\n",
    "\n",
    "You can also bootstrap using many FIPS of your choosing. Here each fip is chooses using uniform random with replacement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "geo_values = [\"42\", \"17\", \"06\", \"36\"]\n",
    "bs = ctc.COVID(geo_values = geo_values, include = [\"cases\"])\n",
    "for data in bs.simulate(block_length = 5, reps = 1000):\n",
    "    plt.plot(data[0][\"cases\"], color= \"tab:blue\", alpha = 0.1)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Weeks\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Cases\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Covid Simulation of FIP: \" + str(geo_values))\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Weighted Random\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we can use weights in the form of a dictionary to choose the FIPS. As you can see 42 is weighted a lot higher than the other states. This is reflected in the graph. You can see that one trend is significantly darker than the others, telling us it has been picked more. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "geo_values = {\"42\":0.9, \"17\":0.033, \"6\":0.033, \"36\":0.034}\n",
    "bs = ctc.COVID(geo_values = geo_values, include = [\"cases\"])\n",
    "for data in bs.simulate(block_length = 5, reps = 1000):\n",
    "    plt.plot(data[0][\"cases\"], color= \"tab:blue\", alpha = 0.1)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Weeks\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Cases\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Covid Simulation of FIPS: \" + str(list(geo_values.keys())))\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
